properties.areaDesc: Wind River Mountains West; Upper Green River Basin Foothills
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 14 at 3:54AM MST until January 14 at 5:00PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...Significant Snow over Western Wyoming Today...

.Snow will continue through late afternoon in the west with bursts
of moderate to heavy snow.

* WHERE...Western Wind River Mountains and the Upper Green River
Basin Foothills.

* WHAT...Periods of snow. Additional snowfall of 2 to 3 inches
today from Pinedale to Bondurant. Additional mountain snowfall
of 4 to 7 inches today.

* WHEN...Until 5 PM Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be difficult. The hazardous conditions
will impact the morning commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Those planning outdoor activities should
be prepared for the snow and cold. Please monitor
JHAVALANCHE.ORG for the avalanche potential across western
Wyoming.
properties.instruction:
The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 PM MST THIS AFTERNOON
